added UTF-16/LE support to PE.getString()

Before this commit, little endian UTF-16 strings -- used commonly in
Windows programs -- were truncated to the first character as in case
of codepoints below 256, every second byte was zero, thus parsing
stopped right after the first character.

This commit adds some heuristics by looking at patterns commonly seen
in ASCII/ISO-8859-1 strings encoded as little endian UTF-16 bytes
while trying to maintain compatibility with other encodings.

append PID to temporary files used for testing

This way, by using the `-j` argument of `make`, tests can be ran in
parallel -- this requires test files to use different names to avoid
race conditions. Running the tests in parallel resulted in more than
100% performance gain (5 instead of 12 seconds for the current set on my
machine).
